The time the session is kept alive after stopping it.
If the session is stopped and then re-started while it is still alive it will be much faster ready than when being completely restarted.
The default value is 1 second.
Negative values will result in a fatal error. Values close to 0 may lead to issues when starting and stopping the session multiple times quickly.
